  <title>Embed a Service-Hosted Video</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Embedding a Service-Hosted Video</h1>
  <section class="tutorial">
    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <h3>Find the Embed Code</h3>
        <p>Log in to your video hosting service and locate the "Share" or "Embed" option for your video. Click this to reveal the embed code.</p>
        <img src="image1.png" alt="Finding embed code">
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Copy the Embed Code</h3>
        <p>Once you've found the code, copy the entire snippet to your clipboard.</p>
        <img src="image2.png" alt="Copying embed code">
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Paste the Embed Code</h3>
        <p>In your website's HTML, paste the copied embed code where you want the video to appear.</p>
        <img src="image3.png" alt="Pasting embed code in HTML">
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Save and View</h3>
        <p>Save the changes to your HTML, upload it to your website, and visit the page to see the embedded video!</p>
        <img src="image4.png" alt="Viewing embedded video">
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="example">
    <h2>Example Embedded Video</h2>
    <p>https://youtu.be/7OYfV83Qa-s?feature=shared</p>
  </section>

</body>
</html>
